title: Pyrochlore (Na$_{3}$Co(CO$_{3}$)$_{2}$Cl) Structure
comments:
This structure was suggested to us by Prof. Joel Helton, United States Naval Academy. This is a pyrochlore-like antiferromagnet, which we loosely define as a structure with magnetic ions on the corners of corner-sharing tetrahedra. 
 We use the structural data taken by (Fu, 2013) at 3.7K
